title: 'Guns don't have capacity to commit crime', says sheriff as 12-year-old arrested in shooting that killed three teenagers
description: A sheriff in Florida went on a rant against gun control while announcing the arrests of a 12-year-old and a 17-year-old in connection with a shooting that left three dead.

title: Two sisters killed in a shooting in the West Bank were British nationals
description: Two women killed in a shooting in the West Bank were British nationals, according to a UK official.

title: Wall Street Journal reporter Evan Gershkovich formally charged with spying in Russia
description: Wall Street Journal reporter Evan Gershkovich has been formally charged with spying in Russia, state-run news agencies have reported today.

title: The 'leaked NATO plans' could prove embarrassing for the US - but useful for Russia
description: Top Secret documents detailing the state of readiness of Ukraine’s forces as well as detailed planning information around equipment inflow, weather, ammunition expenditure, training and much more have been circulating on Telegram and Twitter.

title: Pope to miss Good Friday procession due to 'extremely cold weather' in Rome
description: Pope Francis will miss the Good Friday procession due to "extremely cold weather in Rome", the Vatican said.

title: North Korea defector tells of dramatic escape and reveals what life is really like in secretive state
description: For David, the streets of Seoul are a much longed for safe haven.

title: Investigation into 'leaked secret NATO plans' for war in Ukraine
description: Secret documents disclosing efforts by US, the UK and other NATO allies to build up Ukraine's forces ahead of a new offensive against Russian troops appear to have been leaked online.

title: Israel strikes Lebanon and Gaza following rocket attacks
description: Israeli strikes hit Lebanon and Gaza early on Friday, in response to rocket attacks it blamed on militant group Hamas.

title: Two Tennessee Democrats expelled over gun control protest
description: Tennessee's Republican-dominated House of Representatives has expelled two Democrats over their participation in a gun control demonstration at the state legislature last week.
